    <text>
        <body>
            
            <div1 type="letter">
                
                <pb facs="nei.j4a.22.7-8_0001"/>
                
                <fw type="curatorial">7</fw>
                
                <opener>
                    <dateline>
                        May 19, 1948
                        Boulder, Colo.
                    </dateline>
                    
                    <salute>Dear Mr. Neihardt:</salute>
                </opener>
                <p>Thank you for your friendly reply to my letter and consent to help me. It is difficult to arrange this quick trip but the time is short and I must act. So I shall plan to leave here Monday morning on May 24 and should arrive in Branson by bus on Tuesday morning just before noon. If this is a bad time for me to come, will you please wire me collect as soon as possible?</p>
                
                <p>The English department here is holding me strictly to the idea of a <hi rend="underline">research</hi> work so as it stands now I will be examining the "Indian consciousness" as found in your work. I had wished to attempt a more broad and critical paper but I am very much interested in the Indian theme especially as it appears in your <hi rend="underline">Song of the Messiah</hi>.</p>
                
                <p>Am looking forward to our talks</p>
                <closer>
                    <salute>Sincerely,</salute>
                    <signed>Bill Lemons</signed> 
                </closer>
                
            </div1>
            
            
            <div1 type="envelope">
                
                <pb facs="nei.j4a.22.7-8_0002"/>
                
                <ab type="return">
                    <hi rend="caps">W.</hi> Lemons
                    556 University Ave.
                    Boulder, Colo.
                </ab>
                
                <fw type="curatorial">8</fw>
                
                <ab type="postmark">
                    BOULDER MAY 19
                    6 PM
                    1948
                    COLO.
                </ab>
                <figure>
                    <figDesc>3 Cent Stamp</figDesc>
                    <p>UNITE<unclear reason="missing">D</unclear> STAT<unclear reason="missing">ES</unclear> POST<unclear reason="missing"/> THOMAS JEFFER<unclear reason="missing">SON</unclear> 3 CENTS</p>
                </figure>
                
